musicVideos.title: Baroochs Boots
musicVideos.description: Gotham is still in danger, the Bat-signal is still on, but something is very, very wrong. Crime can wait. Dignity cannot. Somewhere between heroism and humiliation, a legend is struggling to get his footing.

musicVideos.title: The Ballad of MYS
musicVideos.description: He left on a horse, stayed for the adventure, and now even the birds can’t decide if it’s history or a hallucination — some flights need wings, others just need determination.

musicVideos.title: The Robin
musicVideos.description: A brooding figure searches the cliffs for a missing sidekick, while rogue babies start smacking anyone in sight - pipe organs echo in churches, priests sweating, and faith feeling oddly necessary.

musicVideos.title: The Killing Joke
musicVideos.description: He stalks the rain‑slicked streets, laughter and grief colliding in every step, a man haunted by faces he barely remembers - and the city trembles beneath the shadow of his fractured soul.

musicVideos.title: Batman Begins
musicVideos.description: He wakes at dawn, broods in the mirror, tests grappling hooks, counts batarangs, lectures a mannequin, wonders if the Batmobile needs a wash and spends half the morning making sure Alfred didn’t eat all the pancakes.

From lattes to latex, this is the untold saga of a caped crusader chasing the dream. Batman battles bad tips, bad grades, and bad trades - only to realize vengeance doesn’t come with dental, and someone’s still gotta clean the cave.
